==English==
===Noun===
'''[[mortal]] [[sin]]'''

# In [[Roman Catholic]] [[theology]], a mortal sin is a grave matter, such as [[murder]] or [[blasphemy]], and is committed with the full knowledge and deliberate consent of the [[sinner]]. The committing of such a [[heinous]] sin causes a complete loss of [[grace]] and leads to [[eternal damnation]] unless [[absolve]]d.

====Synonyms====
* [[capital vice]]
* [[cardinal sin]]
* [[seven deadly sins]]

